@startuml
title KiTicket — local Docker Compose deployment
node "Browser\nhttp://localhost:5173" as Browser
node "frontend\nNginx :8080" as Frontend
node "backend\nNestJS :3000" as Backend
database "postgres:17\ncontainer :5432" as Postgres
collections "redis:7\ncontainer :6379" as Redis
queue "rabbitmq:3\ncontainer :5672\nmanagement :15672" as Rabbit
component "seed\none-shot backend image" as Seed

Browser --> Frontend
Browser --> Backend : /api via frontend proxy\nor direct local API use
Frontend ..> Backend : API proxy
Backend --> Postgres
Backend --> Redis
Backend --> Rabbit
Seed --> Postgres

note bottom
Compose exposes host ports 3000, 5173, 55432, 56379,
55672 and 15672 by default (some are configurable).
end note
@enduml

